Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiling water and put
on high heat. Bring back to the boil.

Add @salt{1/2%tsp} and the @linguine{200%g}. Cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Save some of the water to use in your sauce!

== Saute ==

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} over
high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden all over, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Vegetables ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Chop the bottom 2cm off the @asparagus{100%g}(bottom 2cm chopped off and discarded)
and discard. Cut the asparagus widthways into 3cm long pieces.

== Sauce ==

Once the mushrooms and bacon are golden, stir in the garlic for ~{30%seconds}.

When the pasta has ~{3%minutes} left, add the asparagus to the water.

Once the asparagus and pasta is drained, stir the @reserved pasta water for the
sauce{100%ml}, the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @chicken stock powder{1} into the
mushrooms.

Stir to dissolve the stock powder, then remove from the heat.

Stir the drained pasta and asparagus, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}
and @?truffle powder{} into the sauce and gently toss to coat.

> TIP: Add another splash of pasta water if the sauce is still a bit thick!

== To Finish ==

Season to taste with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Share between your bowls and dig in!